00:03.664 --> 00:08.684
So hari tu kita orang tanya korang. So saya akan pilih 5 random questions from
Instagram and also thread.

00:08.784 --> 00:12.124
Okay, so let's go with the first one. What is calorie deficit?

00:12.404 --> 00:16.184
Calorie deficit ni happens when you consume fewer calories than your body burn.

00:16.384 --> 00:19.884
Padang kita perlukan certain amount of calories to maintain its weight.

00:20.064 --> 00:26.324
So if you eat less than that, your body will start using the stored energy,
contohnya fat, which leads to weight loss.

00:26.324 --> 00:34.864
Calorie deficit boleh terjadi bila you eating fewer calories, contohnya you
portion control, kurang minum air bergula, minum air masak lebih, ataupun
burning more calories.

00:35.104 --> 00:41.084
Maksudnya through physical activities lah, exercise like cycling ke, running ke,
ataupun combination of both.

00:41.244 --> 00:49.044
The key here is about safe, effective and sustainable approach. Maksudnya
calorie deficit you tu 500 to 750 calories per day.

00:49.284 --> 00:56.024
So but if you do too much too soon, you will get fatigue, cravings, muscle loss
and we don't want that.

00:56.204 --> 01:01.264
Okay, next one. I'm a medical officer just like you, still in service with the
ministry.

01:01.264 --> 01:08.384
I dream of becoming like you, having extra certs in various fields but how do I
start? Where do I find extra info with regards to this matter?

01:08.484 --> 01:15.944
Okay, first of all, don't be like me. Be so much better than me. I'm still a
work in progress and I believe you can do so much better than me.

01:16.264 --> 01:22.584
So but here is how I start. I start with something that I love. So first thing,
you kena start dengan something that you love.

01:22.724 --> 01:28.404
Something that brings you joy every time you do it. Something you passionate
about. You must know what you love.

01:28.404 --> 01:31.164
But if you don't know, now is the best time to explore.

01:31.324 --> 01:36.324
Exploring is fun. You just cuba macam-macam. Don't worry about what people might
say about you. You just cuba je.

01:36.444 --> 01:40.204
Okay, until you find something that you're so passionate about and go from
there.

01:40.344 --> 01:46.124
So how do I get all this information is simply by googling and asking my
friends, us around.

01:46.284 --> 01:53.744
So I think from there, you boleh tahu, oh okay, so this ada cert for this and
you ask people, oh yang ada cert tu, is it worth it?

01:53.744 --> 01:59.364
You know, things like that and open yourself to any opportunities even if it
doesn't involve money.

01:59.996 --> 02:04.616
Okay so the last one is how to start strength training with your five-year-old
son. This is so

02:04.616 --> 02:10.236
interesting. There are a few things that you need to focus on. Fun, skill
development and movement.

02:10.236 --> 02:16.196
Okay so how to do it? Make it a game. For example, animal movement like bear
crawl, frog jump,

02:16.196 --> 02:19.556
one more superhero workout like hawk smash.

02:20.032 --> 02:25.832
Kids will benefit from play-based activities, bodyweight exercises, and learning
coordination.

02:25.832 --> 02:27.792
Okay, so the next one is use bodyweight.

02:27.792 --> 02:29.712
For example, like playing, right?

02:29.712 --> 02:32.832
You make a game like who can hold the longest.

02:32.832 --> 02:34.392
And another one is squat.

02:34.392 --> 02:38.272
So like squat is pretending that you sit on an invisible chair.

02:38.272 --> 02:40.032
Remember to keep it short and fun.

02:40.032 --> 02:42.592
10 to 15 minutes is enough.

02:42.592 --> 02:45.072
Last but not least, make it a challenge, not a chore.

02:45.072 --> 02:50.432
If the kids feel like it's work out or chore, they don't want to play.

02:50.432 --> 02:52.392
So we want them to play.

02:52.392 --> 02:55.952
We want to let them play around without thinking that it's a workout.

02:55.952 --> 02:57.432
So I hope this helps.

02:57.432 --> 03:02.112
Okay, the next one is can you go for a run when you had a low-grade fever?

03:02.112 --> 03:04.312
The short answer is no. Here's why.

03:04.312 --> 03:07.592
Okay, fever is a temporary increase in body temperature

03:07.592 --> 03:10.072
that's usually caused by an infection.

03:10.072 --> 03:13.832
When you run or exercise, your body temperature will increase

03:13.832 --> 03:14.952
which makes your fever

03:14.952 --> 03:15.792
even worse.

03:15.792 --> 03:19.792
You are at risk of dehydration and your immune system will strain

03:19.792 --> 03:21.952
because it's fighting an illness.

03:21.952 --> 03:24.832
So if you put like added physical stress on it,

03:24.832 --> 03:27.392
so it will strain your immune system even more.

03:27.392 --> 03:31.232
When you have a fever, your muscle strength, your endurance drop.

03:31.232 --> 03:34.072
So this will decrease the precision and coordination.

03:34.072 --> 03:38.712
So all of this will increase the risk of injury even more.

03:38.712 --> 03:41.152
So if you have a fever, I know how it feels like.

03:41.152 --> 03:42.192
You feel like you're burning, right?

03:42.192 --> 03:42.912
You don't go running.

03:42.912 --> 03:43.952
But it's okay.

03:43.952 --> 03:44.752
Rest well.

03:44.752 --> 03:46.752
Seek medical help if you need to.

03:46.752 --> 03:49.552
And once you get the mum, you're well, just go for a run.

